Ships in and around New York Harbor, many unidentified, but some with visible names, such as: 
                        African Prince; 
                        Ariosa of New York (tug) [photographed 1950]; 
                        Domfront; 
                        Esso Tug No. 3, Wilmington, Delaware (tug); 
                        Helen Buchanan (tug); 
                        Heredia, New York [photographed 1949]; 
                        Mauretania; 
                        Morro Castle [as wrecked near Asbury Park, N.J., in 1934]; 
                        Queen Elizabeth; 
                        Revere (tug); 
                        Santa Clara; 
                        Santa Sofia; and 
                        W. F. Dalzell (tug). Includes general views of the harbor, Manhattan docks, and infrastructure.
